Description: Handle of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp with Helios head symbol.
Curator's comments: Only known from Petrie's drawing in his Journal, 1884-5, p.59, 12? It is close to British Museum 1925,0119.258, but perhaps not close enough for identity to be confirmed, nor with Cairo, Egyptian Museum 26048. Name, Klearchos.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0740)
